commit.message:
python: run cleanup of TCP connection handler tasks earlier

This includes a simple cleanup mechanism in the Python interop task's
main loop to clean up TCP connection handler tasks that have already
returned. Previously, the Vec of JoinHandles grew without bounds, with
things only being cleaned up at task shutdown.

commit.message:
network: ensure no stray references to PyBytes remain in TcpStream.read

This fixes a memory leak where `bytes` objects returned by TcpStream.read
previously were never garbage collected due to a leaked reference.

commit.message:
expose original source address of WireGuard UDP packets in TcpStream

The source socket of WireGuard UDP packets (i.e. the socket address of
the WireGuard client *outside* the WireGuard tunnel) can now be accessed
with `TcpStream.get_extra_info("original_src")`.
